
From the following table, write a SQL query to find the details of those salespeople who live in cities other than Paris and Rome. Return salesman_id, name, city, commission.Programming

Sample table: salesman

 salesman_id |    name    |   city   | commission 
-------------+------------+----------+------------
        5001 | James Hoog | New York |       0.15
        5002 | Nail Knite | Paris    |       0.13
        5005 | Pit Alex   | London   |       0.11
        5006 | Mc Lyon    | Paris    |       0.14
        5007 | Paul Adam  | Rome     |       0.13
        5003 | Lauson Hen | San Jose |       0.12

-- Selecting all columns from the 'salesman' table
SELECT *
-- Specifying the table to retrieve data from ('salesman')
FROM salesman
-- Filtering the results based on the condition that 'city' is not in the specified list ('Paris' and 'Rome')
WHERE city NOT IN('Paris','Rome');
